headline: Should You Buy the Highest-Yielding Dow Stock After the Market Sell-Off?
summary: The markets have gotten turbulent, with the Dow Jones Industrial Average (DJINDICES: ^DJI) off by a touch more than 11% from its early-year peak.  If you're looking for high-yield stocks, this sell-off could be your chance to hunt for new investment opportunities.  What does the highest-yielding Dow component do?
